Healthcare System Web Application :

Overview :
The Healthcare System is a lightweight web application designed to manage patients, doctors, and appointments. 
It provides a simple and user-friendly interface for healthcare administrators to perform CRUD operations 
(Create, Read, Update, Delete) efficiently. The project is built using HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, JavaScript, and 
Local Storage, making it fully client-side and easy to run without any backend server.

1. Doctor Management :
=> Add new doctors with their name, specialization, and available time slots.
=> Edit existing doctor details.
=> Delete doctor records.
=> Ensure appointments are scheduled only within the doctor’s available time slots.

2. Patient Management :
=> Add new patients with name, age, gender, phone, email, and medical notes.
=> Edit or delete existing patient records.
=> Search patients by name or phone number.

3. Appointment Management :
=> Book appointments for a patient with a selected doctor.
=> Select date and available time slots dynamically based on doctor availability.
=> Prevent double booking for the same doctor at the same time.
=> Update appointment status: Booked, Completed, Cancelled.
=> Filter appointments by date or status.

4. User Interface :
=> Responsive navigation bar with links to Dashboard, Patients, Doctors, and Appointments.
=> Clean table-based view for patients, doctors, and appointments.
=> Modal pop-ups for adding or editing records.
=> Status badges for quick identification of appointment states.
=> Time slot management strictly follows doctor availability.

5. Technologies Used :
-> HTML5 – Page structure.
-> CSS3 & Bootstrap 5 – Responsive design and styling.
-> JavaScript & jQuery – DOM manipulation and event handling.
-> Local Storage – Client-side data storage without a backend server.
-> Bootstrap Modals – For forms and pop-ups.

6. Folder Structure :
healthcare-frontend/
│
├─ index.html                # Dashboard page
├─ doctors.html              # Doctors management page
├─ patients.html             # Patients management page
├─ appointments.html         # Appointments management page
│
├─ css/
│   └─ styles.css            # Custom styles and colours
│
├─ js/
│   ├─ data.js               # Common data and Local Storage functions
│   ├─ doctors.js            # Doctor CRUD logic
│   ├─ patients.js           # Patient CRUD logic
│   ├─ appointments.js       # Appointment CRUD logic
│   └─ common.js             # Utility functions (getDoctorName, getPatientName)
│
└─ readme.txt                # Project documentation

7. Usage :
<> Open the project in a browser by opening index.html.
<> Navigate to Doctors to add doctors and define their availability.
<> Navigate to Patients to add patient records.
<> Navigate to Appointments to book appointments:
   * Select a patient, doctor, date, and time slot.
   * Only available time slots of the selected doctor will be displayed.
   * Status can be updated after completion or cancellation.
<> All data is stored locally in the browser using Local Storage.

8. Key Functionalities : 
# Dynamic dropdowns for doctors and patients.
# Validation checks for empty fields and invalid data.
# Time slot conflict detection.
# Editable records with pre-filled modal forms.
# Filter and search features for efficient management.
